  "text": "The producer and W. H. Lung member makes his remix of the This Is Happening track officialLCD Soundsystem’s James Murphy, June 2025 (Xavi Torrent/Redferns)LCD Soundsystem have shared an official edit of This Is Happening track “Home,” courtesy of Tom Sharkett of Manchester synth-pop band W. H. Lung. DFA will release the song on 12\" vinyl, with an instrumental version on the B-side. The label writes in the product description, “It wasn’t really hiding, just sitting quietly online. But Tom Sharkett’s edit of ‘Home’ was too good to ignore.” The bootleg came to DFA’s attention via Flo Dill’s Breakfast Show on NTS, the label added. Listen to “Home (Tom Sharkett Edit)” below.LCD Soundsystem are currently in London playing a residency at Brixton Academy. After that, they’ll resume a tour of North America, with TV on the Radio supporting select dates. W. H. Lung’s latest album, Every Inch of Earth Pulsates, came out last year.Read about This Is Happening at No. 52 in “The 200 Best Albums of the 2010s.”Jazz Monroe is a music and culture writer based in London. His work also appears in The Guardian, The Independent, and elsewhere. ... Read More",
